          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The ocean covers 70% of the planet, produces half the oxygen we breathe, feeds 3 billion people, and is the world’s largest carbon sink. What happens beneath the surface affects everyone above it. </p><p>With this impending doom, some people are making plans to go live on a rock in space with temperatures of -100°C. But we say: no beach, no fun.</p>"
          }
        }
